image_analysis.description: A close-up photograph of a wooden double door showing significant physical damage. The wood around the latch and lock area is splintered and gouged, suggesting a forced entry. The door features ornate brass hardware, including a decorative knot-style doorknob and a Medeco brand lock cylinder. There is a long brass push plate on the left door and a matching plate on the right door housing the lock and knob.
image_analysis.layout: Vertical close-up shot focusing on the center seam of a double door.

stamps_or_markings: Bates stamp 'EFTA00000006' in the bottom right corner

document_metadata.subject: Evidence of forced entry/damage to a wooden door

notes: The image appears to be an evidentiary photograph from an investigation, likely related to the January 6th Capitol incident given the context of House Oversight Committee documentation. The wood is severely splintered in two distinct locations along the door frame.
